arch string ACTIVE_Y-->\n|y4=9,9,13,16,31,42,67,90,154,219,319,460,604,890,1152,1541,2098,2720,3379,4223,5459,7845,11735,17067,23247,31762,41941,51632,63623,78950,96972,115842,133240,152202,175032,199198,225330,254526,284706,306096,332648,359371,388257,417632,447746,474559,498923,517832,539569,556708,577041\n\n|yScaleType=log<!--This is the line that makes this plot have a log axis-->\n|yAxisMin = 1<!--Needed to avoid trying to show the values y2, y3 of 0, impossible on log scale because log(0)=-infinity-->\n|yGrid= |xGrid=\n}}\n \t\nThe deaths per day from existing endemic seasonal influenza and pneumonia<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gis.cdc.gov/grasp/fluview/mortality.html |title=National Center for Health Statistics Mortality Surveillance System |publisher=Gis.cdc.gov |date=n.d.|accessdate=April 2, 2020}}</ref> is about 551 deaths per day, averaged over seasonal variations. The death rate from COVID-19 exceeded that on March 30, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/covid-data/covidview.html|title=COVIDView|publisher=Gis.cdc.gov |date=n.d.|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=800\n|height=400\n|showValues=\n|xAxisTitle=Date\n|xAxisAngle=-40\n|yAxisTitle=No. of cases\n|legend=Legend\n<!--PLease clipboard copy the \"}x=...\" and \"y1=...\" lines from the log plot of total cases when you update these charts-->\n\n<!--Search string CASES_X-->\n|x= Feb 26, Feb 27, Feb 28, Feb 29, Mar 1, Mar 2, Mar 3, Mar 4, Mar 5, Mar 6, Mar 7, Mar 8, Mar 9, Mar 10, Mar 11, Mar 12, Mar 13, Mar 14, Mar 15, Mar 16, Mar 17, Mar 18, Mar 19, Mar 20, Mar 21, Mar 22, Mar 23, Mar 24, Mar 25, Mar 26, Mar 27, Mar 28, Mar 29, Mar 30, Mar 31, Apr 1, Apr 2, Apr 3, Apr 4, Apr 5, Apr 6, Apr 7, Apr 8, Apr 9, Apr 10, Apr 11, Apr 12, Apr 13, Apr 14, Apr 15, Apr 16\n<!--Search string CASES_Y-->\n<!--y1 NY; y2 NJ; y3 CA; y4 MI; y5 FL; y6 WA-->\n|y1=0,0,0,0,1,1,2,11,22,44,89,105,142,173,216,325,421,613,729,950,1374,2